Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh de Valletort was born about 1058, in Vautorte, Mayenne, France, his father, Godfrey de Valletort, was 24 and his mother, Mrs. Godfrey de Valletort, was 38. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Hugh de Valletort. He died after 1086, in Nether Stowey, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1058–after 1086":"umbes 1058–pärast 1086","1042–1096":"1042–1096","1058–1086":"1058–1086","1060–1086":"1060–1086","1059–Female":"1059–Surnud","1086–Male":"1086–Surnud","1035–1086":"1035–1086","1022–Female":"1022–Surnud","1059":"1059","1058":"1058","1035":"1035","about 1058":"umbes 1058","1022":"1022","after 1086":"pärast 1086","1086":"1086","Aft 1086":"pärast 1086","1042":"1042","1096":"1096","1060":"1060","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Nether Stowey, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Vautorte, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France":"Vautorte, Mayenne, Prantsusmaa","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England":"Nether Stowey, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1058–after 1086":"noin 1058–1086 jälkeen","1042–1096":"1042–1096","1058–1086":"1058–1086","1060–1086":"1060–1086","1059–Female":"1059–Kuollut","1086–Male":"1086–Kuollut","1035–1086":"1035–1086","1022–Female":"1022–Kuollut","1059":"1059","1058":"1058","1035":"1035","about 1058":"noin 1058","1022":"1022","after 1086":"1086 jälkeen","1086":"1086","Aft 1086":"1086 jälkeen","1042":"1042","1096":"1096","1060":"1060","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Nether Stowey, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Vautorte, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France":"Vautorte, Mayenne, Ranska","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England":"Nether Stowey, So